      "guardrails": [
        "Install on all search heads where Unix/Linux knowledge management is required, but keep add-on visibility off on search heads to reduce accidental input execution.",
        "Install on indexers when universal forwarders send this data directly; heavy forwarders can own parsing when they collect and forward the data.",
        "On Universal Forwarders, enable inputs with local configuration files, not with the Splunk Web setup page.",
        "Copy only the input stanzas you need into local/inputs.conf; do not copy the entire default inputs.conf because broad local overrides survive upgrades.",
